US gives 1 million masks to Israel as American troops have to make their own amid COVID-19 outbreak
The US Department of Defense has reportedly supplied 1 million surgical masks to the Israeli regime in order to be distributed among soldiers, despite the fact that the Pentagon has lately introduced a measure requiring personnel to make their own masks to combat the spread of the new coronavirus.
The Israeli English-language Jerusalem Post reported that the masks were procured from China, and a plane carrying the medical stuff intended for Israeli soldiers landed in Ben Gurion Airport on Tuesday night.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm from Hungary and I'm surprised to see at 15:35 that Hungary is not taking proper measures. Let's see the facts (the population of Hungary is slightly less than 10M, can be important for ratio calculation): First 2 confirmed cases in the 4th of March, state of emergency declared in the 11th of March (with 13 confirmed cases only), schools are closed down from 16th of March decided 2 days earlier with only 19 confirmed cases...
The stay-at-home orders are in place since 27th of March (300 confirmed cases in a country close to 10M; it's allowed to go to work if you cannot avoid working from home, for food shopping and for sole sport activity in the neighbourhood where you live).
Even if we assume that not all coronavirus cases were confirmed with testing it was a very fast reaction in my view (lessons learned from the case of Italy though).
As of today (8th of April), there are 895 confirmed cases (real cases can be even 5 times higher estimated from the rather high death ratio).
Some links for backing up the numbers (sorry for Hungarian text, the numbers are international though).
One of the major news portals, with daily confirmed cases shown as a graph till today (move your mouse over the cumulative case graph to see the exact value):
https://index.hu/belfold/2020/04/08/ujabb_fertozottek_magyarorszagon/
Official government site with geographical distribution of the cases (you have to scroll a bit, I don't know where is the same map in the english version if at all):
https://koronavirus.gov.hu/
Biggest risk at the moment is that in the capital city (Budapest) and other bigger cities the virus spreading speeds up. This was announced today by the Mayor of Budapest and government officials together (they are from different political camp).
Don't hesitate to compare what I wrote above with the timeline of actions of your country or other countries and how seriously leaders take the threat.
